decision_conditions:
Reason : 1 - The proposed development would provide an unsatisfactory standared of residential accommodation for the reasons detailed below;
(a) failure to provide outdoor garden amenity space for the two upstairs flats;
(b) failure to meet minimum room size requirements (particularly in relation to the size of all three bathrooms and one bedroom);
(c) failure to provide satisfactory room stacking (particularly in relation to living areas being located above bedroom accommodation);
(d) failure to provide a satisfactory room layout (particularly in relation to a bathroom being accessed directly from a bedroom); and
(e) visual intrusion and loss of light and outlook to the detriment of amenities of neighbouring occupiers by reason of design, siting, scale, bulk, form and proportions of proposed extensions, and failure to meet the aspect value test; all contrary to Policies HS.1, BE.15, BE.23 and BE.24 of the Adopted Unitary Development Plan (October 2003) and the Council's Supplementary Planning Guidance: 'Residential Extensions, Alterations and Conversions (November 2001)'
